	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Estcourt – Eight people were injured when a building collapsed on Harding Street in the Estcourt CBD, KZN Midlands, on Thursday morning, police said. "They were taken to hospital for medical attention," KZN police spokesperson Colonel Thembeka Mbhele said. Five vehicles were also damaged in the incident, said Mbhele. "The cause of the collapse is unknown at this stage," she said. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  